The paper is about optimization of deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The use of genetic algorithm also suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The experiments involve image datasets, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of optimization techniques in control systems suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
